Beta Release Preview of Python 3.7¶

  • Python 3.7 is still in development
  • This is the first of four planned beta release previews
  • The official release of 3.7.0 is planned for June 2018.

All things you need to know about PyData London 2018¶

  • 27-29 April 2018 at the Tower Hotel
  • Fri: Tutorials; Sat-Sun: main event
  • 3 parallel tracks, 1 unconference track (hackathon, sprints, etc.)
  • Beginner's Bootcamp on Wed-Thur

POTM: PdVega: Interactive Vega-Lite Plots for Pandas¶

  • (Props to Giles Weaver for suggesting POTM)
  • Allows you to quickly create interactive Vega-Lite plots from Pandas dataframes
  • Based on visualization specification that allows users to declaratively describe which data features should map to which visualization features using a well-defined JSON schema
